    "Compared to the nEMD distance measures used in the main text however,",
    "these single-answer correlations have the downside of taking a one-against-all approach, not allowing for little variations in the answer levels (e.g.",
    "answer \"C\" being more similar to \"B\" than to \"A\").",
    "The results presented in Figure S15 Table S8: Out-of-bag accuracy of a Random Forest classifier, trained to distinguish between LLM and WVS answer distributions across subpopulations for each question (%) Happiness Politics Religion Trust Next token probabilities GPT-4T 99.4 100.0 100.0 100.0 Llama3-8B 99.6 99.9 99.8 90.1 Llama-3-8B-Instruct 99.9 100.0 100.0 98.5 Llama-3-70B 96.6 99.7 99.1 87.1 Mistral-7B 97.5 100.0 99.6 89.4 Mixtral-8x7B 96.9 100.0 99.6 82.9 Mixtral-8x7B-Instruct 99.9 99.9 99.9 100.0 Full answer generation GPT-3 85.4 92.0 90.5 85.7 GPT-3.5 81.9 98.6 99.9 83.5 Llama-3-8B 84.3 96.2 89.6 75.8 Llama-3-70B 68.5 85.7 87.8 75.0 Mistral-7B 77.4 95.0 99.8 63.5 Mixtral-8x7B 73.9 87.6 96.7 83.0",
    "An alternative regression strategy to the one presented in the main text would be to use as outcome variable the probabilities of LLM-and ground-truth answers, instead of modeling prediction error."
